          "display_title": "Blood Services",
          "timestamp": "17:05"
        },
        {
          "title": "Parallels in the Mincha: Kemitza, Kli Sharet, Holachah, and Placing on the Fire",
          "display_title": "Mincha Parallels",
          "timestamp": "17:24"
        },
        {
          "title": "Kemitza as Preparation: Only a Kohen May Perform It, Reflecting Shechita's Specificity",
          "display_title": "Kemitza Role",
          "timestamp": "18:23"
        },
        {
          "title": "The Mincha Requires a Kli Sharet to Acquire Kedushah Ha-Guf",
          "display_title": "Kli Sharet Need",
          "timestamp": "19:20"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Rav Yehuda's Explanation: How the Mincha Resembles Chatat and Asham",
      "display_title": "Rav Yehuda Explains",
      "timestamp": "20:54",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "The Verse 'Kodesh Kodashim Like Chatat and Like Asham' Permits Dual Interpretation",
          "display_title": "Kodesh Kodashim",
          "timestamp": "20:54"
        },
        {
          "title": "Right-Handed Performance: Mincha Behaves Like Chatat; Left-Handed Like Asham",
          "display_title": "Hand Distinction",
          "timestamp": "20:57"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Shimon Extracts Both Lessons from the Single Verse",
          "display_title": "Dual Extraction",
          "timestamp": "22:29"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Distinguishing When Mincha Chote Is Invalid: The Handful Removed Not for Its Purpose",
      "display_title": "Kemitza Intent",
      "timestamp": "22:43",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "If the Handful Is Removed Not for the Mincha Chote's Purpose, It Is Invalid",
          "display_title": "Purpose Requirement",
          "timestamp": "22:43"
        },
        {
          "title": "This Derives from the Word 'Hi' (It Is) in the Verse, Teaching a Specificity Requirement",
          "display_title": "Specificity from 'Hi'",
          "timestamp": "23:10"
        },
        {
          "title": "Comparison to Chatat: Similar Word 'Hi' Teaches Same Purpose Requirement",
          "display_title": "Chatat Parallel",
          "timestamp": "23:28"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Rabbis' Derivation: Asham and Chatat Both Require Semichah (Leaning)",
      "display_title": "Semichah Requirement",
      "timestamp": "23:51",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Both Chatat and Asham Require Semichah, Suggesting a Hekesh (Analogy) Between Them",
          "display_title": "Hekesh Logic",
          "timestamp": "23:51"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "From Yosef Ben Choni to Rabbi Eliezer: Sacrifices Done for the Wrong Purpose",
      "display_title": "Wrong Purpose",
      "timestamp": "24:56",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Yosef Ben Choni and Rabbi Eliezer Agree: Pesach and Chatat Done Improperly Are Invalid",
          "display_title": "Yosef & R. Eliezer",
          "timestamp": "24:56"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yochanan Expands Their Agreement to All Offerings Done for Pesach or Chatat",
          "display_title": "Yochanan Expansion",
          "timestamp": "25:58"
        },
        {
          "title": "Raba Disagrees on the Extent: They Agree on Pesach, Differ on Other Offerings for Chatat",
          "display_title": "Raba's Limit",
          "timestamp": "26:33"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Machloket Over Pesach: Rabbi Eliezer vs. Rabbi Yehoshua on Intent and Disqualification",
      "display_title": "Pesach Dispute",
      "timestamp": "28:44",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "The Mishnah and Baraita: Pesach Past Its Time Slaughtered Properly, or Other Animals for Pesach",
          "display_title": "Baraita Setup",
          "timestamp": "28:44"
        },
        {
          "title": "Three Categories: Kosher, Invalid (Pesul), and Yotzei HaChiyuv (Fulfills Obligation)",
          "display_title": "Three Categories",
          "timestamp": "29:00"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yehoshua: A Kal va-Chomer from Animals All Year Being Kosher for Pesach's Sake",
          "display_title": "Yehoshua's Kal",
          "timestamp": "33:08"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Eliezer Counters: The Reverse Kal va-Chomer Shows Pesach All Year Is Invalid",
          "display_title": "Eliezer's Counter",
          "timestamp": "34:27"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yehoshua Responds: You Diminish Pesach's Power and Elevate Shelamim's Power",
          "display_title": "Yehoshua Responds",
          "timestamp": "37:42"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Eliezer's Principle: Pesach's Leftovers Become Shelamim, But Shelamim Cannot Become Pesach",
          "display_title": "One-Way Logic",
          "timestamp": "38:51"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yehoshua's Counter: Even More So with Chatat Leftovers and Olah",
          "display_title": "Chatat-Olah",
          "timestamp": "41:04"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Eliezer's Final Principle: Pesach Can Only Be Done at Its Proper Time",
          "display_title": "Time-Specific Rule",
          "timestamp": "46:47"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Hierarchy of Offerings: Ascending in Holiness Permits, Descending Forbids",
      "display_title": "Offering Hierarchy",
      "timestamp": "48:29",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Shimon Achi Azariah's Rule: Lower for Higher Is Kosher, Higher for Lower Is Invalid",
          "display_title": "Hierarchy Rule",
          "timestamp": "48:29"
        },
        {
          "title": "Source: 'Do Not Desecrate the Holy Things' Interpreted Through the Verb Yarimu (Lift Up)",
          "display_title": "Desecration Verse",
          "timestamp": "49:02"
        },
        {
          "title": "Alternative Teaching: Shmuel Uses the Same Verse to Derive the Death Penalty for Eating Tevel",
          "display_title": "Shmuel's Use",
          "timestamp": "50:32"
        },
        {
          "title": "The Tense Yarimu (Future) and Its Double Application to Past and Future Events",
          "display_title": "Tense Lesson",
          "timestamp": "51:47"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Kosher but Not Accepted: The Distinction Between Validity and Fulfillment",
      "display_title": "Valid Not Accepted",
      "timestamp": "52:46",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Zeira's Question: Does Shimon's Opinion Create Offerings That Are Kosher but Not Accepted?",
          "display_title": "Zeira's Query",
          "timestamp": "52:46"
        },
        {
          "title": "Alternative: Perhaps Shimon Holds That Lower for Higher Are Both Kosher and Accepted",
          "display_title": "Two Positions",
          "timestamp": "54:02"
        },
        {
          "title": "Example: Bechor and Ma'aser Sacrificed for Shelamim Are Kosher but Not Accepted",
          "display_title": "Bechor Example",
          "timestamp": "55:05"
        },
        {
          "title": "Shelamim Sacrificed for Bechor or Ma'aser Are Invalid, Because Bechor Is Not Acceptance-Related",
          "display_title": "Reverse Invalid",
          "timestamp": "55:08"
        },
        {
          "title": "The Principle Restated: Only Hierarchy Matters, Not Similarities Between Like Offerings",
          "display_title": "Hierarchy Only",
          "timestamp": "57:26"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Order of Precedence Among Multiple Offerings: Determining Which Offering the Kohen Performs First",
      "display_title": "Order Precedence",
      "timestamp": "58:20",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Shelamim Precede Bechor and Ma'aser Because They Require Additional Services",
          "display_title": "Shelamim Priority",
          "timestamp": "58:20"
        },
        {
          "title": "The Services Required: Matanot Arba, Semichah, Nesachim, Tenufat Chazeh v'Shok",
          "display_title": "Shelamim Services",
          "timestamp": "58:20"
        },
        {
          "title": "The Core Distinction: The Principle of Hierarchy Emerges as Primary, Applied Elsewhere",
          "display_title": "Hierarchy Primary",
          "timestamp": "58:46"
        }
      ]
    }
